quran[37]{c,v,t}:
  19,22,"So she conceived him, and she retired with him into a remote place"
  19,23,"And the labour pains came upon her at the trunk of a palm tree, and she said, 'O that I had died before this, and been forgotten out of mind"
  19,24,"and he called to her from beneath her, 'Grieve not, for thy Lord has placed a stream beneath thy feet"
  19,25,"and shake towards thee the trunk of the palm tree, it will drop upon thee fresh dates fit to gather"
  19,26,"so eat, and drink, and cheer thine eye; and if thou shouldst see any mortal say, \"Verily, I have vowed to the Merciful One a fast, and I will not speak today with a human being"
  19,27,"Then she brought it to her people, carrying it; said they, 'O Mary! thou hast done an extraordinary thing"
  19,28,"O sister of Aaron! thy father was not a bad man, nor was thy mother a harlot"
  19,29,"And she pointed to him, and they said, 'How are we to speak with one who is in the cradle a child"
  19,30,"He said, 'Verily, I am a servant of God; He has brought me the Book, and He has made me a prophet"
  19,31,and He has made me blessed wherever I be; and He has required of me prayer and almsgiving so long as I live
  19,32,"and piety towards my mother, and has not made me a miserable tyrant"
  19,33,"and peace upon me the day I was born, and the day I die, and the day I shall be raised up alive"
  19,34,"That is, Jesus the son of Mary, - by the word of truth whereon ye do dispute"
  19,35,"God could not take to himself any son! celebrated be His praise! when He decrees a matter He only says to it, 'BE,' and it is"
  19,36,"and, verily, God is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him; this is the right way"
  19,37,"And the parties have disagreed amongst themselves, but woe to those who disbelieve, from the witnessing of the mighty day"
  19,38,"they can hear and they can see, on the day when they shall come to us; but the evildoers are today in obvious error"
  19,39,"And warn them of the day of sighing, when the matter is decreed while they are heedless, and while they do not believe"
  19,40,"Verily, we will inherit the earth and all who are upon it, and unto us shall they return"
  19,41,"And mention, in the Book, Abraham; verily, he was a confessors,- a prophet"
  19,42,"When he said to his father, 'O my sire! why dost thou worship what can neither hear nor see nor avail thee aught"
  19,43,"O my sire! verily, to me has come knowledge which has not come to thee; then follow me, and I will guide thee to a level way"
  19,44,"O my sire! serve not Satan; verily, Satan is ever a rebel against the Merciful"
  19,45,"O my sire! verily,. I fear that there may touch thee torment from the Merciful, and that thou mayest be a client of Satan"
  19,46,"Said he, 'What! art thou averse from my gods, O Abraham? verily, if thou dost not desist I will certainly stone thee; but get thee gone from me for a time"
  19,47,"Said he, 'Peace be upon thee! I will ask forgiveness for thee from my Lord; verily, He is very gracious to me"
  19,48,"but I will part from you and what ye call on beside God, and will pray my Lord that I be not unfortunate in my prayer to my Lord"
  19,49,"And when he had parted from them and what they served beside God, we granted him Isaac and Jacob, and each of them we made a prophet"
  19,50,"and we granted them of our mercy, and we made the tongue of truth lofty for them"
  19,51,"And mention, in the Book, Moses; verily, he was sincere, and was an apostle,- a prophet"
  19,52,We called him from the right side of the mountain; and we made him draw nigh unto us to commune with him
  19,53,"and we granted him, of our mercy, his brother Aaron as a prophet"
  19,54,"And mention, in the Book, Ishmael; verily, he was true to his promise, and was an apostle,- a prophet"
  19,55,"and he used to bid his people prayers and almsgiving, and was acceptable in the sight of his Lord"
  19,56,"And mention, in the Book, Idris; verily, he was a confessors prophet,- a prophet"
  19,57,and we raised him to a lofty place
  19,58,"These are those to whom God has been gracious, of the prophets of the seed of Adam, and of those whom we bore with Noah, and of the seed of Abraham and Israel, and of those we guided and elected; when the signs of the Merciful are read to them, they fall down adoring and weeping"